Full Description: Kloog was founded in 2014 by twin brothers, Adib and Niaz, who dreamt of working together from an early age. Both were fascinated by computers growing up and loved the idea of building things, so they pursued similar but separate paths in engineering. Adib was excited about designing hardware and Niaz was passionate about developing software. After building products in the mobile and consumer electronics space for well over a decade, they decided to pursue their dream. Kloog is a stealth mode IoT and Wearables startup that built an intelligent micro-services analytics cloud platform and hardware platform (Kloog Technology).  Our platform applied deep learning to understand collected sensor (structured) and conversation (unstructured data) to provide unique actionable insights.  The cloud platform was built on top a technology stack which included: Mesos, Spark, MLib, Flink, TensorFlow, scikit-Learn, CEP, Vert.x, Redis, Kafka, Blockchain, Zeppelin, and others.  The hardware platform was designed for building low-cost, power-efficient IoT and Wearable devices to work optimally with our cloud platform, completing an end-to-end ecosystem. Thank you to our team, advisors, investors, and partners. Kloog Inc. joined Facebook in January 2017.

Description: Robin Hood Camp, is only seven years away from a major ownership milestone.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: The ownership of a family business is something that can be passed down from generation to generation. With this passing down, comes family traditions of ownership and leadership that simply can't be maintained when a business falls out of a family. For Robin Hood Camp Director Rick Littlefield, a major ownership milestone is just several short years away. The Robin Hood Camp is on a quest for 100 years of ownership by only two generations of a family. The milestone is so impressive, because years of research has yet to uncover any other business or organization that was successfully operated for 100 consecutive years with just two generations of family leadership. Rick Littlefield explains this accomplishment is one that has never been seen before, and that's much of why he's so eager to reach this seven-year gold. Rick Littlefield has successful run the Robin Hood Camp, following his father, for decades. He has maintained many leadership and ownership policies passed down from his father, the founder. Rick Littlefield sates that it would be an honor for the entire Littlefield family to reach this milestone. The Robin Hood Camp Maine currently has 93 years of family tradition under its belt. The camp, currently directed by Rick Littlefield and passed to him by his father, offers one of the most dynamic programs in summer camping for kids. Kids are selected from around the world to take part in the camp and practice more than 35 activities and sports. Rick Littlefield explained that each child is carefully interviewed before admission to ensure an exceptionally friendly camp experience.  Some of the traditions carried down in the camp's nearly 100 years of existence are a remarkable sense of community, camper diversity, and camper freedom to choose their own activities. Rick Littlefield explained that world-renowned counselors, who provide positive experiences for campers year after year, are another time-honored tradition.  "The Robin Hood Camp has been one of the top camps in the country since 1928," Rick Littlefield said. "With all of these years comes experience and tradition that can't be rivaled by other camps." Rick Littlefield described that he looks forward to completing the quest of reaching 100 years of ownership between his father and himself. He explained that this unprecedented achievement is one that will be celebrated among his family and at the camp.  "We know these next seven seasons of camping are going to fly by," Rick Littlefield concluded. "They always do with all of the adventure and excitement that takes place here at Robin Hood Camp. We look forward to keeping this camp in the family for another 100 years too."

Description: Realy is a mobile first real estate platform with a suite of apps and tools that empower real estate agents, companies and homebuyers.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: While delivering accurate property listings through a primarily mobile and cloud platform, Realy also provides the opportunity for real estate businesses, agents, and brokers to easily create the mobile presence that is vital to success in the industry. Realy is a smart and easy way for real estate agents to reach their clients via today's most popular channels: mobile phones and smart devices.  Using the Realy Mobile App platform, agents can create their own personal branded app for their real estate business with no need to program, buy expensive development tools, or be tech savvy.  Our system is simple, user-friendly, quick and affordable; we do the heavy lifting for you. For homebuyers, the relationship with their real estate agent key to the home buying process. It is one that requires trust and communication, as it deals with a primary human need - housing.  We use the latest technology to efficiently make this connection.  With Realy, every agent is present to homebuyers at all times via their smartphones. We provide detailed information for over 1.2 million properties (updated daily) with beautifully displayed photos, local community information, customizable search filters, and more, all seamlessly delivered in a user-friendly mobile app that is free to download from the App Stores. The direct contact feature allows homebuyers to connect instantly with listing agents, and find the right real estate professional for their needs.  Whether you're a homebuyer or an agent, Realy brings everything you need for success to the palm of your hand.
